function Start(sEventName, idActor, nUserParam)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever1, true)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever2, true)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever3, true)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever4, true)
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)
	--Lever 1 operation moves all pieces to the opposite state
	Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(idPuzzleA)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(idPuzzleB)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(idPuzzleC)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(idPuzzleD)
	
	--disable all levers while puzzle pieces are moving
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever1, true)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever2, true)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever3, true)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever4, true)
	Hydra.Wait(2)
	
	--if after operation, the puzzle pieces are all solved, then open door, otherwise turn levers back on
	if (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleA)) and (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleB))
	and (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleC)) and (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleD)) then
		Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(idDoor)
		Hydra.EventSend("OpenSesame", idSelf)
	else
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever1, false)
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever2, false)
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever3, false)
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever4, false)
	end
end

function Start(idActor, fRange, idActorDetector)
	--set up the initial puzzle state
	tPuzzleBlocks = {idPuzzleA, idPuzzleB, idPuzzleC, idPuzzleD}
	--randomly turn one on or off. NOTE: no matter what's the initial state of each piece, it's guaranteed that there's a solution, base on some linear algebra magic.
	for i=1, 4, 1 do
		local intFlag = Hydra.GetRandomInt(0,1)
		Hydra.Wait(Hydra.GetRandomFloat())
		if intFlag == 1 then
			Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(tPuzzleBlocks[i])
		end
	end
	--if all puzzle pieces ended up at the solved position, flip the third one 
	Hydra.Wait(1)
	if (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleA)) and (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleB))
		and (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleC)) and (not Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleD)) then
			Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(idPuzzleC)
	end
	--if all puzzle pieces ended up at the unsolved position, flip the third one
	if Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleA) and Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleB)
		and Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleC) and Hydra.ActorGizmoIsDoorOpen(idPuzzleD) then
			Hydra.ActorGizmoOperate(idPuzzleC)
	end
	
	--turn all pieces back on to be operate-able when player get closer
	Hydra.Wait(1)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever1, false)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever2, false)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever3, false)
	Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idLever4, false)
end
